// v1.8+ regression (issue 3): two libs both export `User` but with
// different fields. Pre-fix the importer's `imported_schemas` keyed
// by the *bare* `User`, so last-write-wins lost one of the two field
// sets — `u.name` would be reported as UnknownReferenceType because
// the surviving entry was lib_b.User (no `name` field). Post-fix the
// key is `a.User` / `b.User`, and the field-tail walker resolves
// each side correctly.
//
// EXPECTED: 0 `UnknownReferenceType` for `u.name` or `v.email`,
// 0 `MainReturnTypeMismatch` (body is Int matching `-> Int` return).
#import a from "./lib_a.relon"
#import b from "./lib_b.relon"
#main(a.User u, b.User v) -> Int
u.id
